title: [95. Unique Binary Search Trees II](https://leetcode.cn/problems/unique-binary-search-trees-ii/)
content:
| English | 简体中文 |
95. Unique Binary Search Trees II Description Given an integer n, return all the structurally unique BST's (binary search trees), which has exactly n nodes of unique values from 1 to n. Return the answer in any order.
 
Example 1:
Input: n = 3 Output: [[1,null,2,null,3],[1,null,3,2],[2,1,3],[3,1,null,null,2],[3,2,null,1]] Example 2:
Input: n = 1 Output: [[1]]  
Constraints:
1 <= n <= 8 Related Topics Tree Binary Search Tree Dynamic Programming Backtracking Binary Tree Similar Questions Unique Binary Search Trees Different Ways to Add Parentheses
